---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Walton-on-Thames.org — Who We Are"
  description="About Walton-on-Thames.org — an independent community guide to Walton-on-Thames, Hersham and Whiteley Village, built and maintained by a local resident."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <ol class="breadcrumbs">
          <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
          <li aria-current="page">About</li>
        </ol>
      </nav>
      <h1>About This Site</h1>
      <p>An independent community guide to Walton-on-Thames, Hersham and Whiteley Village.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container about-layout">
      <article class="prose">
        <h2>Who runs this site?</h2>
        <p>Walton-on-Thames.org is a personal passion project built by a local resident who wanted a single, well-organised online guide to this part of Surrey — the kind of site that actually helps you find things, rather than sending you down a rabbit warren of generic directories and outdated listings.</p>

        <div class="about-author-placeholder">
          <div class="author-photo-placeholder" aria-hidden="true">👤</div>
          <div>
            <p><em>Owner bio to be added here — name, connection to the area, why you built the site. This is the most important trust signal on the page; make it genuine and personal.</em></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>What this site is (and isn't)</h2>
        <p>This is an <strong>independent community resource</strong>. It is not:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Affiliated with Elmbridge Borough Council</li>
          <li>A Visit Surrey or official tourism board site</li>
          <li>A paid PR platform for businesses</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Independence is a feature, not a bug. It means we can be direct about what's good, flag things that aren't working, and write about the area the way a well-informed local would — not the way a tourism marketing department would.</p>

        <h2>How listings work</h2>
        <p>Every listing in the directory is researched using publicly available information — business websites, official directories, Google Maps, and firsthand knowledge. We don't accept payment for basic listings.</p>
        <p>We aim to verify each listing before publishing, but things change. If you notice an error, please <a href="/contact/">get in touch</a> or use the "Suggest an edit" link on any listing page — we genuinely read and act on corrections.</p>
        <p>Each listing shows a <strong>last verified date</strong> so you can see how recent the information is.</p>

        <h2>Photography</h2>
        <p>All photography on this site (unless otherwise credited) is original photography of Walton-on-Thames, Hersham and Whiteley Village. No stock imagery. The photos show the area as it actually is.</p>

        <h2>Getting involved</h2>
        <p>If you have a local business that should be listed, a community event that needs publicising, or a story about the area worth telling — please <a href="/contact/">get in touch</a>. This site is most useful when it reflects the full breadth of local life, and that requires input from local people.</p>
        <p>You can also <a href="/advertise-your-business/">add or claim your business listing</a>.</p>

        <h2>Technical</h2>
        <p>This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a>, hosted on <a href="https://pages.cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Pages</a>, and uses Cloudflare Web Analytics (privacy-friendly, no cookies required). No personal data is stored without your knowledge.</p>
      </article>

      <aside class="about-sidebar">
        <div class="info-card">
          <h2>Quick links</h2>
          <ul class="about-links">
            <li><a href="/contact/">Contact us</a></li>
            <li><a href="/advertise-your-business/">List your business</a></li>
            <li><a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy policy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/accessibility-statement/">Accessibility statement</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card disclaimer-card">
          <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
          <p>Walton-on-Thames.org is an independent community resource. While we take reasonable care with accuracy, information may be out of date. Always verify time-sensitive details (opening hours, event dates, prices) directly with the business or organisation concerned.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-author-placeholder {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(11,36,46,0.04);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1.5px dashed rgba(11,36,46,0.15);
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .author-photo-placeholder {
    font-size: 3rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 64px;
    height: 64px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: rgba(11,36,46,0.06);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .info-card {
    background: var(--color-white);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .info-card h2 {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .about-links {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .about-links a {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .about-links a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .disclaimer-card p {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .about-sidebar { order: -1; }
  }
</style>
